      "document_id": "DOC-HC-001",
      "title": "Q1 2026 Acquisition Strategy - Proposed Merger with Vertex Industries",
      "classification": "highly_confidential",
      "owner": "Emily Johnson (CFO)",
      "last_updated": "2025-12-22",
      "content": "CONFIDENTIAL - BOARD EYES ONLY\n\n1. Transaction overview\n   Proposed structure: all-stock acquisition of Vertex Industries at an implied\n   valuation of approximately USD 480M (1.2x revenue multiple).\n\n2. Strategic rationale\n   Vertex's analytics platform complements our enterprise SaaS suite and unlocks\n   cross-sell into 1,200 mid-market accounts. Estimated $42M run-rate cost\n   synergies within 18 months of close.\n\n3. Key risks\n   - Antitrust review likely in the EU (Phase II possible)\n   - Retention risk: 14 senior Vertex engineers hold unvested equity\n   - Financing: requires additional $120M debt facility\n\n4. Timeline\n   - Term sheet target: 2026-01-15\n   - Signing: 2026-02-28\n   - Public announcement: 2026-03 (post HSR clearance)\n\n5. Approvals required\n   Board approval, Audit Committee review, and antitrust counsel sign-off are all\n   mandatory before any external disclosure."
    },
